                </div>
                <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Installing Arsenal Vault on Windows 11</h1>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">A step-by-step guide to downloading and installing the Arsenal Vault Desktop application on your Windows 11 computer.</p>
            </header>

            <!-- Overview -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-amber-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                            <i class="bi bi-info-circle text-amber-600 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Before You Begin</h3>
                            <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm">Windows may display a security prompt when installing Arsenal Vault. This is normal for new applications. The steps below will guide you through the installation process safely.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="mb-10">
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Need browser access instead?</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">This guide is for the Windows Desktop app. If you are on macOS, a work computer, a tablet, or just want browser access with automatic backups, use the hosted Cloud version instead.</p>
                    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
                        <a href="https://app.arsenalvault.com/register?utm_source=arsenalvault.com&utm_medium=windows_install_cloud_alt&utm_campaign=free_account" class="gradient-gold text-av-dark px-5 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-center hover:opacity-90 transition">Create Free Account</a>
                        <a href="../security.html" class="border-2 border-av-gold text-av-gold px-5 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-center hover:bg-av-gold hover:text-av-dark transition">Review Security</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Step 1 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                    <span class="w-8 h-8 gradient-gold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-av-dark font-bold text-sm">1</span>
                    Download the Installer
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Visit the Arsenal Vault download page and click the <strong>Windows Desktop</strong> download button. Your browser will download a file named <code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">ArsenalVault-Setup.exe</code>.</p>
                <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4">
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">The file will typically appear in your Downloads folder or at the bottom of your browser window.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Step 2 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                    <span class="w-8 h-8 gradient-gold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-av-dark font-bold text-sm">2</span>
                    Run the Installer
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Double-click the downloaded file to start the installation. Windows will display a security screen — this is expected.</p>
                
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">You'll see a screen that says "Windows protected your PC"</h3>
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
                        <!-- Placeholder for SmartScreen screenshot -->
                        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-dashed border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
                            <i class="bi bi-shield-exclamation text-blue-400 text-4xl mb-2"></i>
                            <p class="text-blue-600 text-sm">Windows SmartScreen prompt</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">This message appears because Arsenal Vault is a new application. It's safe to proceed — your data stays encrypted on your local machine.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Step 3 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                    <span class="w-8 h-8 gradient-gold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-av-dark font-bold text-sm">3</span>
                    Click "More info"
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">On the Windows security screen, click the <strong>"More info"</strong> link. This reveals additional options.</p>
                
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                            <i class="bi bi-hand-index text-gray-600 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">Click "More info"</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">This text link appears below the warning message</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                        <!-- Placeholder for More info screenshot -->
                        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-dashed border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
                            <i class="bi bi-arrow-right-circle text-blue-400 text-4xl mb-2"></i>
                            <p class="text-blue-600 text-sm">Click "More info" to reveal the Run button</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Step 4 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                    <span class="w-8 h-8 gradient-gold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-av-dark font-bold text-sm">4</span>
                    Click "Run anyway"
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">After clicking "More info," a <strong>"Run anyway"</strong> button will appear. Click it to proceed with the installation.</p>
                
                <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
                        <!-- Placeholder for Run anyway screenshot -->
                        <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-dashed border-green-200 rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
                            <i class="bi bi-play-circle text-green-400 text-4xl mb-2"></i>
                            <p class="text-green-600 text-sm">Click "Run anyway" to start installation</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">The Arsenal Vault installer will now launch.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Step 5 -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
                    <span class="w-8 h-8 gradient-gold rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-av-dark font-bold text-sm">5</span>
                    Complete the Installation
                </h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Follow the installer prompts to complete the setup:</p>
                
                <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-av-gold mt-1"></i>
                        <span class="text-gray-700">Accept the license agreement</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-av-gold mt-1"></i>
                        <span class="text-gray-700">Choose your installation location (default is recommended)</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-av-gold mt-1"></i>
                        <span class="text-gray-700">Click "Install" and wait for the process to complete</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-av-gold mt-1"></i>
                        <span class="text-gray-700">Click "Finish" to launch Arsenal Vault</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                            <i class="bi bi-check-lg text-green-600 text-xl"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Installation Complete!</h3>
                            <p class="text-green-800 text-sm">Arsenal Vault is now installed. You can find it in your Start menu or on your desktop. Your data is stored locally and encrypted with AES-256 encryption.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Troubleshooting -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-wrench text-av-gold mr-2"></i>
                    Troubleshooting
                </h2>
                
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <details class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                        <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 font-medium text-gray-900">
                            The "More info" link doesn't appear
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-gray-600 text-sm">
                            <p>If you only see a "Don't run" button, make sure you're clicking directly on the blue "More info" text, not elsewhere on the dialog. The text may be small — look for it below the main warning message.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                    <details class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                        <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 font-medium text-gray-900">
                            Windows blocks the download entirely
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-gray-600 text-sm">
                            <p>Some browsers may block the download. Try right-clicking the download link and selecting "Save link as..." or temporarily disable your browser's download protection in settings.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    
                    <details class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                        <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-50 font-medium text-gray-900">
                            Antivirus software flags the installer
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-6 pb-4 text-gray-600 text-sm">
                            <p>Some antivirus programs may flag new applications. You can temporarily disable your antivirus during installation, or add an exception for Arsenal Vault. The application is safe and does not contain malware.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Security Note -->
            <section class="mb-10">
                <div class="bg-av-dark rounded-xl p-8">
